description: *** THIS CAR IS PHYSICALLY LOCATESD IN SOUTHERN CA ***    This is an original California Black Plate car: Genuine, factory original 1966 Mustang GT A-code 289ci V8- 225hp coupe with the original door tag! Meticulously restored to original, this car is finished in Ivy Green Metallic complemented by her Black Crinkle Vinyl and Black Rosette Vinyl, Standard Interior. According to In Search of Mustangs (the definitive registry of vintage Mustangs), of the approximately 65,000 surviving Mustangs listed in the registry, this car is one of just 1081 surviving 289 A-code coupes that are recorded in the registry. Based on consensus estimates of 15% GT production, this car is one of just 162 surviving factory-produced 1966 GT coupes.     It comes finished in code correct fresh Ivy Green Metallic paint job by California West Coast Paint and Body Shop in Los Angeles, CA in December 2016. Great pains were taken to bring this car back to its original state with the help of Paul Crosswhite, the Mustang M.D in Castaic, CA (some know him as the Mustang Ranch... Our source of ORIGINAL parts for this restoration).     This restoration is centered around a like-new drive train:    1. Professionally-rebuilt date-correct 289 V8 and C4 automatic transmission by Automobile Racing Sports Cars, Ohio.  2. Engine fully disassembled and magna fluxed  3. New bearings  4. New pistons, cylinders honed .020 over  5. New camshaft  6. New water pump, fuel pump, and timing chain.   7. Cylinder heads reconditioned  8. Hardened valve seats (for use with modern fuels)  9. Valve job  10. Reconditioned original rocker arms and springs, exhaust manifolds, and starter    This specimen is a TRUE factory GT, as evidenced by:    1. Factory fog lights that also control rear tail lights  2. Oversized master brake cylinder  3. Front disc brakes with Kelsey Hayes 4-piston calipers  4. Original Kelsey Hayes proportioning valve  5. A-code engine  6. Tight-ratio 16:1 power steering box  7. Oversized 13/16 front sway bar  8. Reinforcement plates for exhaust hangers under rear seat  9. Rear brake hose hanger in correct location on undercarriage  10. Dual exhaust with chrome trumpet tips  11. Reinforcement bars inside rear frame rails for exhaust pipe hangers  12. 5-gauge instrument bezel  13. Constant-power relay for fog lights mounted on brake pedal support brace  14. GT emblems on front fenders in place of running horses  15. Pin stripes running the length of the car, with M U S T A N G pin letters  16. GT logo gas cap  17. Rocker panel and quarter panel moldings not present  18. Special rear valence for exhaust tip exit    The engine compartment was stripped to bare metal and given it a fresh coat of paint. Likewise for a number of other parts under the hood - brackets, braces, the original steering box, ETC.    ENGINE and DRIVETRAIN:    - Freshly rebuilt 289 4v V8 225HP A code engine with less than 1000 miles.  - Edlebrock carb with electric choke.   - Freshly rebuilt C4 Automatic transmission, also with less than 1000 miles on it.  - New reproduction correct suspension and springs from CJ  - Original, restored Power Steering Pump and Control valve from Chockostang in Illinois.  - New Power steering slave cylinder and hoses  - New Speedo Cable  - New Transmission cooling lines  - Original driveshaft stripped to bare metal and given a fresh coat of black paint.  - The original Master brake cylinder was restored and used with new brake lines.  - New rear brake cylinders.  - The original Steering box was restored  - The original brake proportioning valve was reconditioned  - Original windshield wiper pump is present as well as the original wiper fluid bag.  - Pertronix electronic ignition, FlameThrower coil, new plugs and cables.  - New battery and tray.  - New solenoid.  - New voltage regulator.  - New engine compartment wiring harness    EXTERIOR    - Freshly painted original Ivy Green Metallic color  - New reproduction styled steel wheels from Kentucky Mustangs  - Original, re

description: For sale in our Nashville showroom is a built beauty, a 1964 Ford Fairlane 500 Thunderbolt tribute. With only 1,200 miles on the drivetrain rebuild, it's fresh and ready to show and go! This '64 Fairlane for sale is the epitome of what was seen during the dawn of muscle cars, shoving the biggest engine possible in the smallest car possible. Powering this tribute Ford Thunderbolt for sale is a 410 cubic inch stroker small block Ford V8 engine. With big cubes in a small block package, this roller Windsor engine is impressive, to say the least! Backing the feisty small block is a stout built TCI 3-speed automatic transmission, which just begs to be ran through the gears! Attached to a ratchet shifter and outfitted with a manual valve body, you get the full racing experience when cruising around in the 1964 Fairlane for sale. With a 4.11 geared Ford 9" rear end, this Ford Fairlane for sale is more than eager to throw to power to the pavement! The exterior is a real throwback, with an aggressive teardrop style hood, which looks right at home with the simplistic and muscular look of this Thunderbolt tribute for sale. With an exterior of white with blue accents, this is a real retro muscle car. All the way down to the stock trim and factory style steel wheels, this Fairlane has more nostalgia than you can shake a stick at! The interior is no different, with blue vinyl that highly compliments the white exterior. The blue vinyl and carpet adorns the cab and is almost soothing. With a warm breeze blowing through your hair while you're cruising around town with the windows down, this hot rod is almost like laying on the beach by the ocean. Especially, when you're trashing from stoplight to stoplight, making waves in the fast and furious Ford! The interior is a real blast from the past and the only sign that this isn't your granny's Fairlane are the aftermarket switches, gauges, and the awesome ratchet shifter. Options on this 1964 Ford Fairlane for sale, include: Vinyl interior, hub caps, radial tires, and seat belts. Whether you're looking for a show cruiser, street bruiser, or simply a far-out grocery get'r this 1964 Ford Fairlane 500 for sale is right up your alley! For more information please call the Nashville showroom at 615-213-1800 or e-mail us at Nashville@GatewayClassicCars.com.

description: The 1965 Ford Mustang is a timeless classic.  So when you can get this icon looking completely vintage on the outside, but with an upgraded A/C interior and more powerful V8 under the hood, it's the best of everything in one affordable coupe.

A Mustang all dressed in gloss black certainly makes you the dark horse wherever you arrive.  But it takes more than luster to create the desire you see here. Bodywork is well done, creases are crisp, and everything lines up nicely to remind us all why we love this icon.  Plus, the bumpers, badging, and trim are all straight and complete, which is why this overall package is so impressive.   You can tell there have been some nice investments in retaining the stock appearance, right down to the stylized wheel covers.

But inside the upgrades are a bit more obvious.  Nothing goes better with a black exterior than a red interior, and so when the outside was switched to the dark hue, the inside got a sinisterly aggressive color makeover.  So while the red seat covers look stock, and they have a feeling of quality to let you know that they are much younger than '65.  And the carpeting and door panels match its vibrancy.  You get great factory items like heat/defrost sliders and a center console.  Plus, there are nice upgrades like the Grant sports steering wheel and an AM/FM/CD stereo with aux hookup for modern music players.

Under the hood is the legendary 289 cubic-inch V8, and it has been upgraded for both style and substance.  Radiating from the dark engine bay are great elements like the shiny air topper and freshly painted blue valve covers.  Plus, the V8's performance has been enhanced with a Holley four-barrel carburetor, Edelbrock intake, newer radiator, and long tube headers that feed a rumbling dual exhaust.  On the road, the three-speed automatic transmission, power steering, and front disc brakes come together to make sure that this enhanced V8 is one pony that you can easily corral.

You're looking at a two-owner American icon that's been so well cared for you even get the owner's manual.  A Mustang that's turnkey with all the right vintage looks and all the right upgrades is irresistible.  So if you want to make it yours, hurry up and call today!

description: *** THIS CAR IS PHYSICALLY LOCATESD IN SOUTHERN CA ***    This is an original California Black Plate car: Genuine, factory original 1966 Mustang GT A-code 289ci V8- 225hp coupe with the original door tag! Meticulously restored to original, this car is finished in Ivy Green Metallic complemented by her Black Crinkle Vinyl and Black Rosette Vinyl, Standard Interior. According to In Search of Mustangs (the definitive registry of vintage Mustangs), of the approximately 65,000 surviving Mustangs listed in the registry, this car is one of just 1081 surviving 289 A-code coupes that are recorded in the registry. Based on consensus estimates of 15% GT production, this car is one of just 162 surviving factory-produced 1966 GT coupes.     It comes finished in code correct fresh Ivy Green Metallic paint job by California West Coast Paint and Body Shop in Los Angeles, CA in December 2016. Great pains were taken to bring this car back to its original state with the help of Paul Crosswhite, the Mustang M.D in Castaic, CA (some know him as the Mustang Ranch... Our source of ORIGINAL parts for this restoration).     This restoration is centered around a like-new drive train:    1. Professionally-rebuilt date-correct 289 V8 and C4 automatic transmission by Automobile Racing Sports Cars, Ohio.  2. Engine fully disassembled and magna fluxed  3. New bearings  4. New pistons, cylinders honed .020 over  5. New camshaft  6. New water pump, fuel pump, and timing chain.   7. Cylinder heads reconditioned  8. Hardened valve seats (for use with modern fuels)  9. Valve job  10. Reconditioned original rocker arms and springs, exhaust manifolds, and starter    This specimen is a TRUE factory GT, as evidenced by:    1. Factory fog lights that also control rear tail lights  2. Oversized master brake cylinder  3. Front disc brakes with Kelsey Hayes 4-piston calipers  4. Original Kelsey Hayes proportioning valve  5. A-code engine  6. Tight-ratio 16:1 power steering box  7. Oversized 13/16 front sway bar  8. Reinforcement plates for exhaust hangers under rear seat  9. Rear brake hose hanger in correct location on undercarriage  10. Dual exhaust with chrome trumpet tips  11. Reinforcement bars inside rear frame rails for exhaust pipe hangers  12. 5-gauge instrument bezel  13. Constant-power relay for fog lights mounted on brake pedal support brace  14. GT emblems on front fenders in place of running horses  15. Pin stripes running the length of the car, with M U S T A N G pin letters  16. GT logo gas cap  17. Rocker panel and quarter panel moldings not present  18. Special rear valence for exhaust tip exit    The engine compartment was stripped to bare metal and given it a fresh coat of paint. Likewise for a number of other parts under the hood - brackets, braces, the original steering box, ETC.    ENGINE and DRIVETRAIN:    - Freshly rebuilt 289 4v V8 225HP A code engine with less than 1000 miles.  - Edlebrock carb with electric choke.   - Freshly rebuilt C4 Automatic transmission, also with less than 1000 miles on it.  - New reproduction correct suspension and springs from CJ  - Original, restored Power Steering Pump and Control valve from Chockostang in Illinois.  - New Power steering slave cylinder and hoses  - New Speedo Cable  - Ne.
